<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06331059 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06331059 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  US; HOUSING; SALE; INCREASE; STATISTIC  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  Sales of existing, detached homes nationwide edged up 1 percent in October,the first increase in four months, an industry group reported Monday.;   Butin California, sales on a seasonally adjusted, annual basis sagged to theirlowest level since January, down 2 percent. Most of the decreases were postedin Southern California counties, while Northern California's urban areas,including Santa Clara County, showed modest increases.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Business  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  U.S. HOME SALES RISE 1%; STATE FIGURE FALLS 2%  </HEADLINE><TEXT>     The statewide median price of detached homes dropped 1.1 percent, to$196,440.;   The conflicting data shows that though consumers remain verynervous about purchasing homes, lower prices and low interest rates aredrawing first-time buyers to the market, real estate officials said.;   TheCalifornia Association of Realtors, which reports closed escrows, said itsmembers in Santa Clara County sold 8.5 percent more detached homes on anon-adjusted basis in September than October. The median sales price was$253,840, down .5 percent from September.;   Although Santa Clara Countytrailed behind the Southern California housing markets over the summer, itappears to be stronger this fall. Closed escrows were off between 4 and 9.5percent in October in Los Angeles, Orange, Riverside and San Bernardinocounties.;   As reported earlier this month, the San Jose-area alsoexperienced a slight increase in pending sales in October. Pending salesdipped in more affluent areas of the mid-Peninsula. Pending sales reflectprices and sales agreed to that month; closed escrows generally reflect dealsmade 30 to 90 days before the reporting month.;   The National Association ofRealtors reported that 3.15 million units closed escrow nationwide on aseasonally-adjusted annual rate, up for the first time since June. The medianprice declined slightly to $99,700.;   The California Association of Realtorssaid 372,900 units closed escrow in the state, off 2 percent. But sales ofmore affordable condominiums and townhouses increased 10 percent overSeptember. The median price dropped price .7 percent to $145,610.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  MARY ANNE OSTROM, Mercury News Staff Writer  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   911126  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Tuesday  </DAY><MONTH>  November  </MONTH><PG.COL>  9C  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  316  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Tuesday, November 26, 199100331059,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>